CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1778073067
OL,3,CBan early morning pre-flight pints at
OL,4,Cairports, Ryanair boss says
OL,6,F"We are reasonably responsible, but
OL,7,Fthe ones who are not responsible, the
OL,8,Fones who are profiteering off it, are
OL,9,Fthe airports who have these bars open
OL,10,Fat five or six o'clock in the morning
OL,11,Fand during delays are quite happy to
OL,12,Fsend these people as much alcohol as
OL,13,Fthey want because they know they're
OL,14,Fgoing to export the problem to the
OL,15,Fairlines," he said.
OL,17,FBeing drunk on a plane is a criminal
OL,18,Foffence and can be punished by a fine
OL,19,Fof up to #5,000 and two years'
OL,20,Fimprisonment.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@JO]
